i’langa continues to support the shopper community by ensuring that critical products and services are available to those who need them. The well-being of tenants, shoppers and employees are of paramount importance and to that effect, the mall management is closely monitoring the development of the Covid-19 situation. i’langa Mall has taken the necessary precautionary measures in accordance with the World Health Organisation and the relevant South African and local health authorities. The mall endeavours to stay abreast of all new developments to keep its shopper community informed at all times.  Providing a safe environment, as i’langa remains open, is the first priority. The mall has taken heed of all recommended precautions, and cleaning of its common areas is taking place more regularly and rigorously, using the prescribed alcohol-based or antibacterial disinfectants. Tenants of i’langa Mall have also responded well and have implemented their own internal precautions and regimes. Over and above these added safety measures, the mall urges shoppers to follow the prescribed hygiene guidelines such as washing your hands thoroughly and regularly, avoiding physical contact such as shaking hands, refraining from touching your face, and coughing or sneezing into your elbow, to name but a few. Notices can also be found in all the ablution facilities in i’langa.  Stay informed with the National Institute for Communicable Diseases that provides regular updates on the Covid-19 situation in South Africa. The Department of Health’s Support WhatsApp line is 060-012-3456. All you need to do is save the number on your phone, and send a WhatsApp that says “hi” to activate the menu. i’langa Mall says its thoughts are with those impacted.     